   Azure topics 
   
 * ACR               (Azure container registry)
 * AD                (Azure active directory)
 * Storage account
 * Keyvault
 * VPN               (Virtual Private network)                        
 * DNS               (Domain name system)
 * AKS               (Azure kubernetes service)
 * VM                (Virtual machine)
 
 
 ******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
 1. ACR (Azure Container registry service)
    ->
    . It is a private docker registry service
    . they can store private docker container images
    . you can also integrate with AKS
     
     
     
    "How to create and use ACR"
     1st create Azure account 
     Go to azure portal -> create resources -> container registry -> fill your details -> after deployment -> go to resources -> repositries -> ***It should be Empty***
     Now come to terminal -> sudo az login -> u get a code paste it in microsoft.com/device login -> sudo az acr login --name <your container name> -> (Before this you should have a docker image    
     to push) -> sudo docker tag nginx akshayacrdemo.azurecr.io/nginx -> sudo docker push akshayacrdemo.azurecr.io/nginx -> go check in the repositry u should have "nginx" there -> Your done
     
     
*******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
 2. AD (Active directory)
    ->    
    . It is similar to IAM 
    . User and group management
    . User provisioning 
    . And more



   "How to create and use AD"
    Go to azure portal -> create resources -> Active directory -> fill those details -> after deployment -> overview -> In that you'll be having Users and groups -> Come to users -> Add user
    fill those details -> Give the required access to user (Role) -> Come to groups -> fill those and create group -> now assign the group with users -> Your done 
    
    
*******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
 3. Storage account 
   -> 
   . they can store unstructured and structured data 
   . they store containers, fileshare, tables, queues
   . this can stores unlimited containers
   . they can store azure data
   
   
   
   "How to create and use storage account" 
    Go to azure portal -> Create resources -> Storage account -> fill those details -> after deployment -> Your done 
    
    *******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
 4. Keyvault
   ->
  . It enables users to securely store and manage sensitive data like keys, passwords, certificates, and other sensitive information
  . It is used as a solution for key management. It makes it simple to generate and manage encryption keys for your data.
  
  
   "How to create and use Keyvault"
    Go to azure portal -> Create resources -> Keyvault -> fill those details -> after deployment -> check and add keys, secrets and certificates in it -> Your done
   
   
 
*******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
 5. VPN (Virtual private network) 
   -> 
  . It is a service that uses a specific type of virtual network gateway to send encrypted traffic between an Azure virtual network and on-premises locations over the public Internet
  . Secure Connectivity
  . Remote Access
  . It is simlar to VPC in AWS.
  
  
  "How to create and use VPN"
   Go to azure portal -> Create resources -> Virtual networks -> fill those details -> create subnets -> create -> connect to virtual gateway -> Your done 
                                                                                                                                { |-> Create resources -> virtual gateway -> fill those deatils->    
                                                                                                                                      attach virtual network -> Your done } 


*******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
 6. DNS (Domain name system)
   -> 
   . It is a hosting service for DNS domains that provides name resolution by using Microsoft Azure infrastructure
   . The Domain Name System (DNS) locates and translates website domain names into internet protocol (IP).
   
   
   
   "How to create and use DNS"
    Go to azure portal -> Create resources -> DNS zone -> fill those details -> create -> add resources (add public ip to your website) -> come to terminal -> az login -> nslookup www.akshay.org   
    ns1-32.azure-dns.com. (this will vary accordingly) -> Your done 
    
    
