 8. VM (Virtual machine)
   ->
   . A virtual machine is like a physical computer but it is actually a digital version of it
   . Virtual machines can be used to run the various apps and software on operating systems that are not made originally for them
   . It is similar to EC2 instances
   
   
   "How to create and use VM"
    Go to azure portal -> Create resources -> Virtual machine -> fill those details (image, admin deatils, inbound rules, disks, networks) -> create -> go to remmina (Linux) -> give username &  
    passwords -> get into new server -> Your done
    
    
     
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
   
    
